## 🧪 Simulate a Brute-Force Attack (Demo)

With the server running, open a **new terminal**, activate the virtual environment, and run:

```bash
python test_attack.py
```

This script sends 10 rapid fake login attempts and shows when the AI Shield blocks the attacker.

Expected output:
```
=======================================================
   Ai-Basesd-Password-Attack-Detection — Brute Force Attack Simulation
=======================================================

Attempt  1 | Status: 200 | URL: http://127.0.0.1:5000/login
          ✅ Wrong password accepted (not blocked yet)
...
Attempt  6 | Status: 200 | URL: http://127.0.0.1:5000/login
          🔴 BLOCKED by AI Shield at attempt 6!

Simulation complete.
```

